Doc,<br><br>
I don't know 'bout that... I think there is a rhyme and a reason for it all and bless the stars there are places like this for the freedom to be a passionate about our freedoms as we all are. If nothing else it proves beyond a shadow of doubt that the war in Vietnam will remain a hot war long after the last bullet is fired, long after the last bomb had landed.. it will last as long as there are men &amp; women who have that passion to stand up on the soap box one more time and tell the world what they think. Is it not what the fight was kind of all about in the first place ? Freedom. Small word large price to pay, from all of us. SO the war will rage on and on, between my ears and with those who’s passions about the war are still among the living.. After we are all gone.. MAYBE.. just Maybe the battle will be over.. You think ? I try not to.. it hurts sometimes.<br><br>
 Just my opinion.. I could be wrong...<br><br>
Gary 'J.'
